dynamicalSystems
Class Element

java.lang.Object
  dynamicalSystems.Entity
      dynamicalSystems.Element
Direct Known Subclasses:
Converter, Flow, Stock
public abstract class Element
extends Entity

An Element is the principal part of a Dynamic System. A element is either a flow, or a stock, or a converter. These elements are connected by relationships, that indicates how the elements are interrelated(the equations).

Author:
Wellington Bruno

Field Detail

name

protected java.lang.String name
The object's name

allValues

protected java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> allValues
During the simulation, the element may have different values. This attribute holds all the values that a particular element has, during the simulation

determinants

protected java.util.ArrayList<Element> determinants
A determinant is one Element that determines the value of other element. For example, elementA = elementB + elementC. Then,elementB and elementC are determinants of elementA. To calculate an element's value, is calculate before the value of its determinants. Because of this, it's very important tell which are the element's determinants, to avoid incorrect results on simulation.

ifThenElse

protected IfThenElse ifThenElse
Indicates that to calculate the element's value, must be done an analysis, and the value depends on this analysis. In an IfThenElse equation, if the Condition is true,the result will be the first parameter Case the condition is false, the result will be the second parameter. To adjust this attribute, the user shall call the method setIfThenElse();

released

protected boolean released
Indicates if the element is or not is released to update. This attribute helps on update a element only once,for time interval. When the element is updated, this attribute receives the value false.When the time interval ends up, this attribute is released to update again.

relationship

protected Relationship relationship
relationship save the way how the determinants are connected. For example,given two determinants,what is the equation between them ?

dt

protected static double dt
The time variation. Indicates if the time interval is either 1,or 0.5,or 0.25,or 0.125 .

simulation

protected static Simulation simulation
This static attribute,store all elements created in the simulation and will be useful to manage them (block them,release them),and update their values

lookUp

protected LookUp lookUp
Allow create a table, indicating the output given a input. When the element's result depends on a table,must be used the attribute lookup. To insert values on the table, must be used Row objects. After the table (lookUp)is ready to be used, must be done something like : element.setLookup(objectLookUp); element.connect(elementDeterminant,Relationship.WITH_LOOKUPS);
